BENIN  – The Management of Ambrose Alli Univer­sity (AAU), Ekpoma, has ordered the closure of the university and gave the students 24 hours to move out over what it described as “the roll-over national strike em­barked upon by the Academic Staff Union of Universities (ASUU).” This was contained in a statement signed by Edward U. Aihevba, the Acting Registrar of the University on Monday. The Acting Registrar said, “The Management of Ambrose Alli University, Ek­poma, has on behalf of the Senate, approved the tempo­rary suspension of academic activities in the University as a result of the roll-over national strike embarked upon by the Academic Staff Union of Uni­versities (ASUU). “Consequently, all students are directed to vacate the Halls of Residence on or before mid­night of Tuesday March 22, 2022. “They are to return when the University announces the resumption of academic ac­tivities. “Administrative activities in the University will, howev­er, continue without any inter­ruption. “This is for the Information and guidance of all students, staff and the University com­munity”, the statement further stated.